( FLOW-MATIC was a 1955 business programming language predecessor to COBOL.
  It used English-like statements. The following expresses merge sort logic
  in FLOW-MATIC inspired pseudocode. )

(0) READ-ITEM ARR GIVING 38 27 43 3 9 82 10.
(1) COMPARE ARR-COUNT TO 1 ; IF LESS OR EQUAL GO TO (END).
(2) COMPUTE MID = ARR-COUNT / 2.
(3) SET LEFT-BOUND TO 1.
(4) SET LEFT-END TO MID.
(5) SET RIGHT-BOUND TO MID + 1.
(6) SET RIGHT-END TO ARR-COUNT.
(7) EXECUTE MERGE-SORT WITH LEFT-BOUND AND LEFT-END.
(8) EXECUTE MERGE-SORT WITH RIGHT-BOUND AND RIGHT-END.
(9) EXECUTE MERGE WITH LEFT-BOUND AND MID AND RIGHT-END.
(END) WRITE-ITEM SORTED-ARR.
(STOP) STOP.
